//Cardiovascular risk - ESC Score


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 02 of Cardiac MRI
And I select 'Cardiovascular risk' tab

When I select 'Laboratory parameters' checkbox
Then 'mg/dl' input field is enabled
And 'mmol/l'  input field is enabled
And 'Total cholesterol' input field is enabled
And 'HDL cholesterol' input field is enabled
And 'LDL Cholesterol' input field is enabled
And 'Triglycerides' input field is enabled
And 'Hematocrit in %' input field is enabled

When I select 'Renal insufficiency' checkbox
Then 'eGFR' input field is enabled

When I select 'Arterial hypertension' checkbox
Then 'Current antihypertensive therapy' checkbox is enabled
